<a name="73">[73]</a> Meantone is tuned so that each fifth in Pythagorean intonation is decreased by a quarter of a "syntonic comma" to make the major thirds more in tune, at the cost of the fifth. A Syntonic comma is defined as a Pythagorean major third divided by a just major third, or (81/64)/(5/4), or 81/80, or 1.0125, or 21.506 cents, or near a fifth of a semitone.<br>
